mkruby is a simple shell script to fetch and install the latest 
ruby 1.9.3 or 2.0.0  patch set on OpenBSD 5.3 i386/amd64

requirements:

	devel/libffi
	devel/libyaml
	shells/bash 
	curl
	
usage: mkruby [1.9.3|2.0.0] [fetch|extract|build|install|all]

* Don't forget to tweak the CFLAGS variable for the system you are building on